FW Final AM Process for Lynn Just to let you know that one of the imbalances that kicked out I did figure it outbelieve it or notI have run nominated reports and scheduled quantities reports for all of Axias contracts so that Kathy and myself can look at those on Monday to make sure everything looks alright The final for I was able to figure out and everything was fine I will get this final down if it kills me Original Message From Hoang Joe Sent Saturday October PM To Buchanan John Cc Clapper Karen Washington Kathy Kedwaii Hasan Vakil Kramer Subject Final AM Process for John Karen asked me to send you a note about the problems we encountered with the final AM processing for When Karen submitted the rollover for the first time it kicked out two imbalances One she was able to figure out with Kathys help and the other one she cannot The shipper on K nom at Demarc to K during the ID cycle They were scheduled at Shipper K modified his gas from Demarc from K to different storage However he renom at the full not the amount that was scheduled from ID which was Shipper K did not make any changes to this package If we just looked at the nom screen everything is tied out However we have to consider whats was scheduled In this case the scheduled number for K did not match the final am nomination on K After this transaction was invalidated K the system kicks out another imbalance since K was realigning storage gas to K and we did not invalidate that change Karen also had some problems with not seeing the apply button I think Kathy walked her through the process since I did not We restarted the final AM process after the Timely allocation and completed the cycle around pm Please call if you have questionsconcerns Thanks Joe
